## Commit signing (required for GitHub "Verified")

Commits are SSH-signed locally. GitHub shows **Unverified** until your public key is registered as a **Signing key** (not just Authentication):

1. Open https://github.com/settings/ssh/new
2. Key type: **Signing key**
3. Paste the contents of `C:\Users\Ekrami\.ssh\id_rsa.pub`
4. Save — existing commits become Verified without re-push

Run `.\scripts\show-signing-key.ps1` to print the key and open GitHub settings.
